Subject: CardConnect

Guy,
Hope all is well. Wanted to follow-up
on a number of topics from our call
yesterday.

First, thank you for taking the time to
discuss a potential solution to enable
CardConnect to continue with their
planned acquisition of Merchant Link. I
know you mentioned a variety of
considerations on your end that could
make
this, or any transaction in the near
term that
could
impact the announced
combination of First
Data and
CardConnect, rather challenging. I did
want to emphasize the time sensitive
and
unique nature of this opportunity for
CardConnect.

As a reminder, Merchant Link is a
gateway with direct connectivity to all
the
major card brands for the
hospitality and
restaurant industries. Their technology
is
similar
to Shift4 (although not at all
specific to
gaming) with a large base of
integrated
Point-of-Sale partners.
CardConnect should surpass 200
integrated
P0S partners by the end of
this year so
leveraging this additional
scale of distribution
is quite
meaningful. Merchant Link also has
many thousands
of large enterprise
customers similar
to Shift4,
which would provide a vast
opportunity for CardConnect's security
solutions
(tokenization and P2PE).

I appreciate the willingness to
consider
this
matter. From the CardConnect side,
We
will
do whatever we can to reduce
any concerns
associated with
completing a Merchant Link transaction
prior to the official close between First
Data
and
CardConnect. This could
include escrows,
holdbacks,
indemnifications, etc. We
believe this
is as much a win for First
Data as it is for
CardConnect and my
team is available to
address any issues
that arise.
I
am also available to discuss.

Thank you,

Jared
